    // Real Redlands, CA road network derived from OpenStreetMap (dense downtown + Esri HQ edition).
    //
    // Nodes are actual OSM points with true WGS84 coordinates: real street intersections
    // plus curve vertices chosen by deviation-bounded (Douglas-Peucker) simplification, so
    // no edge strays more than ~4 m from the true road - streets, ramps, and freeway curves
    // all trace their real shape. Edges are real road segments between adjacent kept points;
    // costs are the real along-road distance in km.
    //
    // Coverage: dense downtown Redlands and the area around Esri HQ (arterials down to
    // residential/living streets), reduced to the largest component reachable to Esri HQ,
    // so every one of the 2529 nodes can route to the destination. The graph is
    // undirected (every segment bidirectional); Dijkstra and A* run over it unchanged.
    //
    // Of the 2529 non-destination nodes, 1594 are routable junctions/endpoints and
    // 935 are curve-shape vertices (degree 2) kept only for visual road fidelity.
    //
    // Node 2530 = Esri HQ (380 New York St), the fixed destination, at its true campus
    // coordinate, linked to its two nearest intersections.
    //
    // Total: 2530 nodes, 3187 edges. Generated from OSM data - do not hand-edit.
